node.title: Thousands in Vienna protest Austria's looming lockdown
node.description: The far-right opposition Freedom Party was among those who have called for the protest and vowed to combat the new restrictions.

node.title: School Bus Crash Sees Multiple Deaths in 'Horrific' Collision With Truck
node.description: The bus carried members of a high school band when it was struck by a pickup truck reportedly driving in the wrong direction, killing at least three people.

node.title: Fentanyl-laced marijuana confirmed in Connecticut
node.description: Health officials in Connecticut have issued a warning about fentanyl-laced marijuana, which is being eyed in a rash of overdoses throughout the state.

node.title: Wildfires in California Killed Thousands of Giant Sequoias
node.description: The past 15 months have been devastating for the majestic trees, as fires destroyed an estimated 13 to 19 percent of their population, officials said.

node.title: Was the Kyle Rittenhouse Trial About Race, the Second Amendment or Neither?
node.description: Black Lives Matter protesters, Second Amendment defenders, and legal experts have all weighed in on the trial and its not guilty verdict. Who is right?

node.title: Confidence in Americans' Election Day Choices Plummets Among Independents, Republicans
node.description: Just 37 percent of independents and 46 percent of GOP voters said they now have faith in Election Day choices.
